in Gedaliah, and no man knew it,","year":-588},{"id":"recbYTd4ZlfAheO8f","ref":"Jer.41.5","text":"That there came certain from Shechem, from Shiloh, and from Samaria, even fourscore men, having their beards shaven, and their clothes rent, and having cut themselves, with offerings and incense in their hand, to bring them to the house of the LORD.","year":-588},{"id":"recdJn7jAuGNcbkA3","ref":"Jer.41.6","text":"And Ishmael the son of Nethaniah went forth from Mizpah to meet them, weeping all along as he went: and it came to pass, as he met them, he said unto them, Come to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam.","year":-588},{"id":"recG8VuFRllht0y5u","ref":"Jer.41.7","text":"And it was so, when they came into the midst of the city, that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah slew them, and cast them into the midst of the pit, he, and the men that were with him.","year":-588},{"id":"recn4KcRdyi7TFJr2","ref":"Jer.41.8","text":"But ten men were found among them that said unto Ishmael, Slay us not: for we have treasures in the field, of wheat, and of barley, and of oil, and of honey. So he forbare, and slew them not among their brethren.","year":-588}]}
